    <item>
      <title>约翰逊在与反对派进行最后谈判后赢得众议院议长选举</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/johnson-wins-house-speaker-vote-after-late-talks-with-holdouts</link>
      <description><![CDATA[共和党人迈克·约翰逊在经过最后一刻的一系列谈判后，克服了少数但至关重要的保守派强硬派的阻力，并得到了当选总统唐纳德·特朗普的关键支持，再次当选众议院议长。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/johnson-wins-house-speaker-vote-after-late-talks-with-holdouts</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 19:35:39 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>共和党的约翰逊试图在第一轮选举中扭转局势，赢得议长职位</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/johnson-appears-to-fall-short-of-votes-needed-to-win-speaker</link>
      <description><![CDATA[共和党人迈克·约翰逊似乎未能连任众议院议长，这促使共和党推迟投票，而他和他的盟友则努力扭转选票。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/johnson-appears-to-fall-short-of-votes-needed-to-win-speaker</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 18:36:44 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>波兰因逃犯案件将匈牙利特使从嘉宾名单中除名</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/poland-pulls-hungarian-envoy-from-guest-list-over-fugitive-case</link>
      <description><![CDATA[在波兰总理维克托·奥尔班领导的政府为一名逃亡的波兰反对派议员提供庇护后，波兰撤回了对匈牙利大使参加欧盟主题晚会的邀请。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/poland-pulls-hungarian-envoy-from-guest-list-over-fugitive-case</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 16:51:43 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>“伟大的协议”：特鲁多的保守党对手向特朗普推销能源</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/canada-s-pierre-poilievre-tells-jordan-peterson-he-s-got-great-deal-for-trump</link>
      <description><![CDATA[自赢得美国大选以来，唐纳德·特朗普一直嘲讽加拿大总理贾斯汀·特鲁多，称他为美国第51个州的州长，威胁征收25%的关税，并发泄美国因贸易逆差而被北方邻国欺骗。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/canada-s-pierre-poilievre-tells-jordan-peterson-he-s-got-great-deal-for-trump</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 16:51:41 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>加密货币在华盛顿的政治力量不够统一</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/crypto-lands-in-washington-as-less-than-unified-political-force</link>
      <description><![CDATA[过去几周，从硅谷到华盛顿，加密行业一直在庆祝胜利。随着支持加密的当选总统、新的人工智能和加密沙皇的出现，以及美国证券交易委员会主席加里·根斯勒即将离职，美国数字资产的未来从未如此光明。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/crypto-lands-in-washington-as-less-than-unified-political-force</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 16:35:52 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>拜登否决美国钢铁协议引发众多新问题</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/what-s-next-for-us-steel-after-biden-blocks-japanese-takeover</link>
      <description><![CDATA[美国总统乔·拜登决定阻止新日铁公司以 141 亿美元收购美国钢铁公司，这给这家美国标志性企业带来了新的不确定性，该公司一直是美国国内政治风暴的核心，并加剧了与长期外交盟友日本的紧张关系。拜登于周五宣布了正式决定，此前美国安全审查小组将此案提交给了他，美国钢铁公司的股价因此下跌，交易价格远低于新日铁公司每股 55 美元的报价]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/what-s-next-for-us-steel-after-biden-blocks-japanese-takeover</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 16:32:25 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>拜登阻止新日铁以 141 亿美元收购美国钢铁公司</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/president-biden-blocks-nippon-steel-bid-for-us-steel</link>
      <description><![CDATA[总统乔·拜登阻​​止了美国钢铁公司以 141 亿美元的价格出售给新日本制铁公司的交易，从而终止了这项引发政治风暴和美日紧张关系的备受瞩目的交易。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/president-biden-blocks-nippon-steel-bid-for-us-steel</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 13:09:20 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>欧洲试图与叙利亚建立联系并削弱普京的影响力</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/europe-aims-to-build-ties-with-syria-s-leaders-to-cut-putin-s-influence</link>
      <description><![CDATA[德国和法国外交部长访问大马士革，欧盟加大力度与叙利亚新领导人建立联系，并说服他们减少俄罗斯对这个饱受战争蹂躏的国家的影响。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-03/europe-aims-to-build-ties-with-syria-s-leaders-to-cut-putin-s-influence</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 09:23:10 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>联邦调查局警告伊斯兰国可能利用新奥尔良袭击事件的风险</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-02/new-orleans-attack-shows-enduring-influence-of-islamic-state</link>
      <description><![CDATA[据彭博新闻社获得的评估显示，美国官员警告称，伊斯兰国将试图利用新年新奥尔良致命袭击事件引发更多暴力行为，尽管他们表示没有迹象表明该组织指挥了此次事件。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-02/new-orleans-attack-shows-enduring-influence-of-islamic-state</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 02 Jan 2025 22:25:14 GMT</pubDate>
